In article &lt;2764@medusa.informatik.uni-erlangen.de&gt; eckert@medusa.informatik.uni-erlangen.de (Toerless Eckert) writes:
&gt;Anyway, i don't see the need for discussion here: it doesn't make a
&gt;difference for anyone that the zones are different, or does it - No,
&gt;it does not, as those who can't resolve domainnames from the states
&gt;couldn't even reach the associated nets in germany.

Hog wash...  The fact that I CAN reach certian de hosts whose names and
nameservers do not appear in the stateside zone is what prompted
this whole discussion in the first place.

These arguments about not providing nameservice just because someone 
can't reach the your nameservers are absurd...  You always have some net
somewhere which is unaccessible no matter who or where you are.  Not
providing nameservice dosn't help anything.

The reachability issue should be addressed at the ip leval, insted of
being kluged at the nameserver leval.


brad
    huntting@sel.bldrdoc.gov
    huntting@boulder.colorado.edu

